ally also 95% confidence intervals) that lie below the 45 degree line, while the
opposite applies for relatively high-price contracts.This mirrors the well-docum
ent favorite-longshot bias in betting markets, which has not been recorded previ
ously for relatively short-dated prediction markets such as the one we are looki
ng at. ${}^{6}$Figure 3: Win percentage sorted by price(shaded areas are 95% con
